text: Russell County is a county in the U.S. state of Alabama. As of the 2020 census, the population was 59,183. The county seat is Phenix City. The name is in honor of Colonel Gilbert C. Russell, who fought in the wars against the Creek Indians. Russell County was founded on December 18, 1832. == References == Category:1832 establishments in Alabama Category:Alabama counties
title: Russell County, Alabama
